Serialized Fields

servletDestroyed

boolean servletDestroyed
Flag set by the SlingServletDelegate.destroy() method to indicate the servlet has been destroyed. This flag is used by the #startSling(String) method to check whether the SlingServletDelegate has been destroyed while Sling was starting up.

sling

SlingBridge sling
The Felix instance loaded on SlingServletDelegate.init() and stopped on SlingServletDelegate.destroy().

delegatee

javax.servlet.Servlet delegatee
The map of delegatee servlets to which requests are delegated. This map is managed through the service listener based on servlets registered.
